    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Heavyweight plain- or twill-weave cloth of worsted, cotton, wool, or other fibers, singly or in combination, first made in Bedford, England, characterized by heavy, warpwise cords or stripes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Paño pesado liso o tejido como sarga de lana peinada, algodón, lana u otras fibras, sólo o combinado, fabricado por primera vez en Bedford, Inglaterra. Se caracteriza por cuerdas o bandas pesadas del lado de la urdimbre.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zware, normaal geweven of gekeperde stof van kamgaren, katoen, wol of andere fibers, of een combinatie hiervan. Voor het eerst geproduceerd in Bedford, Engeland en gekenmerkt door zware, verdraaide koorden of stroken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>厚重的平織布或斜織布，由精紡纖維、棉、羊毛或其他纖維單獨或混和製成。最先產於英國貝德福德一地，其特色為厚重，布的細線或條紋呈經向排列。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Schweres Gewebe in Leinwand- oder Köperbindung aus Kammgarn, Baumwolle, Wolle oder anderen Fasern, einzeln oder in Kombination, das zuerst in Bedford, England hergestellt wurde und such durch schwere, in Kettenrichtung verlaufende Schnüre oder Streifen auszeichnet.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
